BT /F2 13.5 Tf 72 451.2 Td (1. Background and aim) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72 430.2 Td (Official labor statistics confirm AI-driven displacement only after a lag of quarters. By then the) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72 415.4 Td (exposed households have already absorbed the financial stress. We ask whether a combined) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72 400.6 Td (AI-exposure and household financial-stress search signal leads realized occupational) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72 385.8 Td (unemployment by one to three months, among the most exposed occupations, across US states,) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72 371 Td (in the generative-AI period. This is a measurement and prediction study, not a causal one. We) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72 356.2 Td (never claim AI caused any specific household's distress.) Tj ET
BT /F2 13.5 Tf 72 323.4 Td (2. Data-access statement \(why we register now\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72 302.4 Td (As of registration we have built, or will build, only the inputs: the exposure composite and the) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72 287.6 Td (search signal. We have not accessed, pulled, summarized, or inspected the outcome series) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72 272.8 Td (\(CPS occupational unemployment\) for the test window. We post this design first, then pull the) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72 258 Td (outcome. That ordering is the credibility claim, so we state it plainly and date it.) Tj ET
BT /F2 13.5 Tf 72 225.2 Td (3. Hypotheses) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72 204.2 Td (-   H1 \(confirmatory, primary\). The combined AI-distress signal at month t is positively related) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72 189.7 Td (    to realized occupational unemployment at t+k, for k of 1, 2 and 3 months, among) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72 175.2 Td (    high-exposure occupations \(top tercile of the exposure composite\). Operationally, the sum of) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72 160.7 Td (    the distributed-lead coefficients over k is positive at the threshold in section 6.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72 146.2 Td (-   H2 \(confirmatory, placebo\). No such lead appears among low-exposure occupations \(bottom) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72 131.7 Td (    tercile\).) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72 117.2 Td (-   H3 \(secondary\). Augmentation-coded search terms do not predict unemployment;) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72 102.7 Td (    substitution-coded terms do.) Tj ET
endstream
