BT /F2 13.5 Tf 72 720 Td (4. Variables) Tj ET
BT /F2 11.5 Tf 72 691 Td (4.1 Predictor: the combined AI-distress signal) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72 673 Td (Two pieces, an exposure layer and a search layer.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72 653.2 Td (Exposure composite. For each SOC-coded occupation we build a composite from three) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72 638.4 Td (published indices: Felten, Raj and Seamans \(AIOE, 2021\); Eloundou, Manning, Mishkin and) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72 623.6 Td (Rock \(GPT exposure, 2023\); and Brynjolfsson, Mitchell and Rock \(suitability for machine) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72 608.8 Td (learning, 2018\), where available. Each index is z-scored across occupations, then averaged) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72 594 Td (with equal weights by default. We roll the occupation scores up to states with BLS OEWS state) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72 579.2 Td (employment shares:) Tj ET
BT /F3 7.7551 Tf 78 556.4 Td (AIExposure_state = sum over occ of \( employment_share[state, occ] x ExposureScore[occ] \)) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72 541.931 Td (The high-exposure group is the top tercile of the composite, employment-weighted across) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72 527.131 Td (detailed occupations. The low-exposure group is the bottom tercile, used as the H2 placebo. The) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72 512.331 Td (confirmatory test \(H1, H2\) runs on these two groups.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72 492.531 Td (Occupation clusters \(the descriptive layer\). For the public cube and for the secondary by-cluster) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72 477.731 Td (breakout we use six SOC major groups, chosen because their exposure varies widely:) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72 457.931 Td (1.  Office and administrative support \(SOC 43\), high exposure) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72 443.431 Td (2.  Computer and mathematical \(SOC 15\), mixed) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72 428.931 Td (3.  Healthcare practitioners \(SOC 29\), low to moderate) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72 414.431 Td (4.  Production \(SOC 51\), moderate) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72 399.931 Td (5.  Transportation and material moving \(SOC 53\), moderate) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72 385.431 Td (6.  Education, training and library \(SOC 25\), moderate) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72 365.931 Td (Search layer. We pull Google Health Trends volumes for an AI-distress ontology in four) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72 351.131 Td (categories:) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72 331.331 Td (-   Displacement awareness: "will AI take my job", "AI replaced me", "job to AI") Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72 316.831 Td (-   Reskilling intent: "reskill from [occupation]", "career change at 40", "learn to code 2026") Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72 302.331 Td (-   Acute distress: "laid off tech", "severance negotiation", "unemployment after layoff") Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72 287.831 Td (-   Adaptation, tracked separately as augmentation rather than substitution: "use ChatGPT at) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72 273.331 Td (    work", "AI tools for [occupation]") Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72 253.831 Td (Each term passes a signal-to-noise screen before it goes live. We normalize each series as) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72 239.031 Td (divergence from a trailing 52-week baseline, with robustness at 26 and 104 weeks, and we pull) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72 224.231 Td (from January 2022 so the divergence is defined from the first test month. Google Health Trends) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72 209.431 Td (is geographic \(state by week\), so the search layer is measured at the state level; the) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72 194.631 Td (occupational content of the test comes from stratifying the outcome by exposure.) Tj ET
BT /F2 11.5 Tf 72 166.831 Td (4.2 Outcome) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72 148.831 Td (Realized unemployment from CPS microdata \(IPUMS-CPS\), computed at the occupation level) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72 134.031 Td (and then aggregated, from the same micro-data, two ways: into the high and low exposure) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72 119.231 Td (groups for the confirmatory test, and into the six clusters for the descriptive cube and the) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72 104.431 Td (secondary breakouts. Monthly, on a 3-month rolling basis to tame CPS sampling noise. The) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72 89.6306 Td (reference period is the survey month. We fix the vintage to first release so revisions cannot) Tj ET
endstream
