BT /F1 11 Tf 72 720 Td (move the result. Robustness brackets: LAUS state unemployment, and national unemployment) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72 705.2 Td (by occupation cluster.) Tj ET
BT /F2 11.5 Tf 72 677.4 Td (4.3 Secondary grounding input \(not in the confirmatory test\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72 659.4 Td (To ground the search signal in real events we compute an exposure-weighted layoff intensity) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72 644.6 Td (from WARN Act notices and BLS JOLTS:) Tj ET
BT /F3 7.7551 Tf 78 621.8 Td (AILayoffIntensity_state,q = sum over event of \( workers x ExposureScore[occ] \) / labor_force_state) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72 607.331 Td (This is a validation and case-study input, not a predictor in the confirmatory regression.) Tj ET
BT /F2 13.5 Tf 72 574.531 Td (5. Analysis plan) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72 553.531 Td (Primary model. A panel distributed-lead regression of occupational unemployment at t+k on the) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72 538.731 Td (standardized signal at t, with leads at k of 1, 2 and 3, group-by-state and month fixed effects, and) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72 523.931 Td (standard errors clustered by state and by exposure group. The decision statistic is the sum of) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72 509.131 Td (the three lead coefficients in the high-exposure group.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72 489.331 Td (Out-of-sample check. The signal-augmented model must also beat an autoregressive baseline on) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72 474.531 Td (RMSE at horizon k, in a rolling-window evaluation.) Tj ET
BT /F2 13.5 Tf 72 441.731 Td (6. Inference criteria \(the number that counts\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72 420.731 Td (-   Primary. The distributed-lead coefficient sum is positive at p < 0.05, two-sided.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72 406.231 Td (-   Multiple comparisons. There is exactly one confirmatory test, the pooled high-exposure) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72 391.731 Td (    lead-coefficient sum. Every by-state, by-cluster and by-k breakout is secondary and reported) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72 377.231 Td (    with Benjamini-Hochberg FDR control at q of 0.10, labeled exploratory.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72 362.731 Td (-   Confirmatory versus exploratory. Anything not named here as confirmatory is exploratory,) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72 348.231 Td (    and labeled as such in the paper.) Tj ET
BT /F2 13.5 Tf 72 315.731 Td (7. Exclusions and suppression) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72 294.731 Td (-   Suppress any cell \(state, exposure group or cluster, and month\) with fewer than 50) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72 280.231 Td (    labor-force respondents in the 3-month pooled window.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72 265.731 Td (-   Flag, but do not drop, any search series below its volume floor: a state-week below the 10th) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72 251.231 Td (    percentile of that term's national distribution is low-confidence. Drop a series only if it is) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72 236.731 Td (    zero or near-zero for more than half the window. Floors can be tightened after we see the) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72 222.231 Td (    volume distributions, never loosened, and any change is documented.) Tj ET
BT /F2 13.5 Tf 72 189.731 Td (8. Sample and period) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72 168.731 Td (All 50 states plus DC. Test window from January 2023 \(post-ChatGPT, the generative-AI) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72 153.931 Td (period\) to the data-freeze month. Search series pulled from January 2022 for the baseline.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72 139.131 Td (Monthly frequency.) Tj ET
BT /F2 13.5 Tf 72 106.331 Td (9. What counts as support, and the kill condition) Tj ET
endstream
